James Anderson  took 4-35 to leave
England needing four wickets to defeat India in their third
cricket Test.  India is 116-6 at lunch on day four at Edgbaston in
Birmingham to trail by 370 runs.  Sachin Tendulkar  scored 40
before being run out.  England yesterday delared on 710-7 after Alastair Cook
scored a career-best 294. India was 224 all out in its first
innings.  England leads the four-match series 2-0 and will replace
India as No. 1 in the International Cricket Councilâ€™s rankings
